definitions.definition: Cold and damp , usually referring to hands or palms.
examples: His hands were clammy from fright.

definitions.definition: The quality of normal skin signs , epidermis that is neither diaphoretic nor dry .

main_definition: Cold and damp , usually referring to hands or palms.
secondary_definitions: ( medicine ) The quality of normal skin signs , epidermis that is neither diaphoretic nor dry .
